1
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,510
This is the map of the park.

2
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:15,890
Let me teach you how to look for it.

3
00:00:16,230 --> 00:00:17,770
First, we need to divide it into

4
00:00:16,430 --> 00:00:22,430
[1997]

5
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,670
a 9 by 10 grid.

6
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:21,800
Why is it 9 by 10?

7
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:25,030
Because I always score 90 on my exams.

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Our current location is right here.

9
00:00:29,030 --> 00:00:30,190
It's a corridor.

10
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:33,960
The corresponding numbers
for the corridor are 3 and 5.

11
00:00:34,150 --> 00:00:35,210
Do you understand?

12
00:00:37,150 --> 00:00:39,410
Then what numbers represent this place?

13
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:43,520
The numbers for this are...

14
00:00:43,550 --> 00:00:44,320
3

15
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,790
and 6.

16
00:00:46,110 --> 00:00:47,920
So it's 36.

17
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:48,810
Correct.

18
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:51,600
This is the small bridge behind us.

19
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:56,350
It's also Bin's favorite hiding spot.

20
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:59,110
These numbers and locations—

21
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:02,010
can you memorize them?

22
00:01:04,349 --> 00:01:04,950
Yes.

23
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,070
Good.

24
00:01:06,790 --> 00:01:08,760
Watch my hand signals later.

25
00:01:09,230 --> 00:01:10,630
You hit wherever I point.

26
00:01:11,430 --> 00:01:11,789
Okay!

27
00:01:12,789 --> 00:01:14,150
Seven.

28
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,430
Six.

29
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,560
Five.

30
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,430
Four.

31
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:23,560
Three.

32
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,280
Two.

33
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:26,400
One.

34
00:01:27,710 --> 00:01:28,840
Are you done hiding?

35
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,450
I'm going to start looking!

36
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:10,580
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

37
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:13,190
[Episode 16]

38
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,020
Well...

39
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,680
Has something happened?

40
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,630
It's my fault. My apologies.

41
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:25,520
I originally wanted

42
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,910
to help out.

43
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,340
I didn't expect

44
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,120
to break the pot

45
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,520
and scare her.

46
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:37,829
I'm really sorry.

47
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,800
My wife is easily frightened.

48
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,870
She gets nervous easily.

49
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,520
You got burned, right?

50
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,130
Let me take you to the hospital.

51
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:50,840
It's fine.

52
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,079
You just stay with your wife.

53
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:54,340
We can go by ourselves.

54
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,570
Don't worry.

55
00:03:56,890 --> 00:03:57,820
I'll be with her.

56
00:03:59,079 --> 00:03:59,560
Okay.

57
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,800
W-Well, I'm sorry about this.

58
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:04,470
If anything comes up later, just...

59
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,730
Just contact me.

60
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,850
Don't worry.

61
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:09,790
We'll be leaving now.

62
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:10,680
Okay.

63
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:22,720
Take care.

64
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:31,240
How are you?

65
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,480
It's fine now.

66
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:39,830
I'm here.

67
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:44,900
Let me take a look.

68
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,140
Bold enough to grab the knife?

69
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:56,950
If I hadn't done that, you would have.

70
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:58,270
In this kind of situation,

71
00:04:58,270 --> 00:04:59,470
it's better if I do it.

72
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:01,870
How are you?

73
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,170
Does it hurt?

74
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:06,320
Now we've become bros in distress.

75
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:12,250
Companions in adversity
have deep affection.

76
00:05:12,530 --> 00:05:13,530
Those are lyrics.

77
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,220
Don't you dislike songs with lyrics?

78
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:23,650
Your playlist is a bit old,
Professor Jiang.

79
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,680
Let's go to the hospital first.

80
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,360
Honey.

81
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:02,830
I'm out.

82
00:06:04,890 --> 00:06:06,850
Don't worry, I'll be right back.

83
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:16,950
Honey, where did you go?

84
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:18,200
Fooling around?

85
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:22,270
If you ever dare to touch her again,

86
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:23,240
I'll kill you.

87
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:34,310
You're sweating so much.

88
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,240
Where did you go?

89
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:39,920
It's too hot.

90
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,320
Come have some water.

91
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:47,600
Play it.

92
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:51,580
I want to hear it.

93
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,000
Mom.

94
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:31,140
Mom!

95
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:32,500
Mom!

96
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,120
Mom!

97
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,720
Someone is hurt.

98
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,720
Save them, quick!

99
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:50,840
Comrade,

100
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:51,550
wake up.

101
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:52,100
Kid!

102
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:52,670
Comrade,

103
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:54,190
-wake up!
-Wake up!

104
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,570
Are you okay?

105
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:57,890
It's likely a suicide by wrist-slashing.

106
00:08:57,890 --> 00:08:58,700
Go get a towel!

107
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,150
Hurry up and bring the car.

108
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,080
Don't touch her.

109
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:06,660
Kid,

110
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:08,350
I'm a police officer.

111
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,150
I'm saving your mom.

112
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:12,030
Don't worry.

113
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:21,320
Don't be afraid.

114
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:51,710
How is it?

115
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,380
Foreigners know their stuff.

116
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:56,960
They only want the best.

117
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:05,030
Give them this.

118
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,200
It's perfect.

119
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,840
Young Master Wen,

120
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:27,480
what do you plan for Jiang Cheng to do?

121
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,440
Young Master Wen?

122
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,040
What's wrong?

123
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:49,670
Is he upset?

124
00:12:51,790 --> 00:12:53,870
People are born different.

125
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:57,010
Wen Lang has been playing the piano
since he was a kid.

126
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:05,150
It's just a piano.

127
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:08,670
It's not that bad.

128
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:18,750
Let me tell you.

129
00:13:19,390 --> 00:13:20,840
This piano is like a person.

130
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,900
If you care about it, it's something.

131
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,230
If you don't,

132
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:26,080
it's nothing!

133
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:27,720
Right?

134
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,160
What did you just say?

135
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,390
I said...

136
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,080
I'm just asking.

137
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,930
Since you let Jiang Cheng
into the production area,

138
00:13:51,930 --> 00:13:54,190
are you planning for him to do something?

139
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,380
When he's seen enough,

140
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:15,480
bring him up.

141
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:43,090
How do you feel?

142
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,280
I don't understand.

143
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:49,310
Boss He sent you to get the goods.

144
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,400
The goods are right here.

145
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:56,380
I just didn't expect you to produce
and sell it yourselves.

146
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:03,070
The finest ingredients

147
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:07,840
often require only the simplest cooking.

148
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:09,000
Is it simple?

149
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:11,440
The hard part is management.

150
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:14,310
Jiang Cheng.

151
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:17,850
I think you've seen it too.

152
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:19,790
Qi is getting old.

153
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,630
Qiu Ye needs to stay by my side.

154
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:24,480
Mr. He

155
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,860
has his own business to attend to.

156
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:29,080
So I am in urgent need of talent now.

157
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,630
I need the right people

158
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,840
in the right positions.

159
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,530
Just tell me what you need me to do.

160
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,510
I want you to stay

161
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,730
and help me move the goods.

162
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:41,530
How's that?

163
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:49,200
Sure.

164
00:15:50,370 --> 00:15:51,000
I have

165
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,010
nowhere else to go anyway.

166
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:06,750
What?

167
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:08,840
Are you upset?

168
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:11,300
I'm just stating facts.

169
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,140
I must be on the police's

170
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:14,600
wanted list by now anyway.

171
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,510
I can't survive without you.

172
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,180
Good thing there's a sanctuary like this.

173
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:21,580
Otherwise, I wouldn't even know how I died.

174
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:28,130
You feel wronged?

175
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,240
What's there to feel wronged about?

176
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,010
I'm here too, aren't I?

177
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:33,680
Look, he feels wronged too.

178
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,240
How do we move the goods?

179
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,050
It's simple.

180
00:16:41,730 --> 00:16:44,030
Give them whatever they want,
as much as they want.

181
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:45,080
Qiu Ye told me

182
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,740
you know this route well.

183
00:16:46,740 --> 00:16:49,150
So I'm 100% confident leaving it to you.

184
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,530
Who is the buyer?

185
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,030
When the time comes, the buyer will

186
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,830
contact you through this phone.

187
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:04,780
I will also contact you
through this phone.

188
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:08,440
There is a bank card linked to this phone.

189
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:10,400
Use it freely.

190
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:11,720
Freely?

191
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,069
Freely.

192
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,510
That sounds like a pretty good deal.

193
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:20,849
Then,

194
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:23,000
Jiang Cheng,

195
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:25,700
I'll take that as a yes.

196
00:17:28,569 --> 00:17:29,740
From now on,

197
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,960
you are Old Scorpion.

198
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:34,400
What do you mean?

199
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,880
Old Scorpion is just a title.

200
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,270
It can be a symbol.

201
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,050
Or it can be a trademark.

202
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,110
Or

203
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,130
when you go to pick up a package,

204
00:17:46,510 --> 00:17:47,960
it can be your pseudonym.

205
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,770
Whoever needs to be,

206
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,880
is him.

207
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:54,110
That sounds casual.

208
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:55,400
The buyer

209
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:59,830
only moves goods through Old Scorpion.

210
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,600
Whoever moves the goods

211
00:18:02,270 --> 00:18:03,510
is Old Scorpion.

212
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:06,070
Wait.

213
00:18:06,770 --> 00:18:08,970
Can I understand it as,

214
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,890
if the deal succeeds,
Old Scorpion takes the money.

215
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:12,270
If the deal fails...

216
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,920
You cannot fail.

217
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:17,670
You have no right to fail.

218
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,700
Killing a police officer.

219
00:18:21,030 --> 00:18:21,830
Making drugs.

220
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:24,750
Drug trafficking.

221
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:27,830
If you get caught...

222
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,730
Understood.

223
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:30,720
If I get caught,

224
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:32,830
I'll be your scapegoat.

225
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:34,230
No, no!

226
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:36,770
You are one of my lives.

227
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:40,070
You are a part of my life.

228
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:41,720
If you die,

229
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:46,380
that would be my biggest loss.

230
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,440
Really.

231
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,790
I'm really curious about something.

232
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:58,350
Was Qi Yan, who died 5 years ago,

233
00:18:58,350 --> 00:19:00,510
also one of your lives?

234
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,240
Why mention him?

235
00:19:10,590 --> 00:19:11,640
I'm just curious.

236
00:19:21,790 --> 00:19:24,160
Curiosity isn't always a good thing.

237
00:19:25,510 --> 00:19:26,720
Let me put it this way.

238
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,000
You and he are different.

239
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:32,320
He was chosen by fate.
You were chosen by me.

240
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:34,350
Chosen by fate?

241
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:36,880
Which ranks higher?

242
00:19:44,590 --> 00:19:45,640
You.

243
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:03,350
Since I am already Old Scorpion,

244
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:04,880
can I negotiate some terms?

245
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:05,510
Speak.

246
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,400
I don't want to fight
unprepared battles anymore,

247
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,750
nor do I want to be treated like a fool

248
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,240
and played around with anymore.

249
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:11,880
Go on.

250
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:13,980
I want to contact the buyer
to move a batch of goods first.

251
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:15,000
It can be a smaller amount—

252
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,230
just to test the waters.

253
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:17,640
I will decide the time and place.

254
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,100
Once that is done,
we can talk about the rest.

255
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,160
Fine.

256
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,200
But things are tense lately.

257
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:24,680
I need to send a few guys to follow you.

258
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,740
No problem, right?

259
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:26,540
No problem.

260
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:27,510
Of course not.

261
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,640
Dahua has to follow me.

262
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,270
Sure.

263
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:31,480
You have my word.

264
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,590
Also,

265
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,570
I can't live without the internet.

266
00:20:34,830 --> 00:20:37,200
Playing cards, gaming, eating hot pot—

267
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,260
you can satisfy all these, right?

268
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:40,680
Cheng,

269
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,870
do you think you are on vacation?

270
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:43,920
Boss,

271
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:46,670
life is short,
we must enjoy it while we can.

272
00:21:03,860 --> 00:21:05,320
Enjoy it while we can, huh?

273
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,720
Fine, I'll agree to that.

274
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,400
I will arrange

275
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,130
a relatively nice room for you.

276
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:10,400
But as you can see,

277
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:13,210
every room here has surveillance cameras.

278
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:15,250
Including when you're eating

279
00:21:15,590 --> 00:21:16,550
and sleeping.

280
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:19,350
You'll have to be watched

281
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,550
24 hours a day.

282
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,440
There are no blind spots.

283
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,900
Are you okay with that?

284
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,720
Whether I can accept it or not,

285
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,250
didn't you guys just see it?

286
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,750
If I am not wrong,

287
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:32,350
this phone should have something like

288
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:35,150
location tracking
and voice monitoring systems,

289
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:35,680
right?

290
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,160
Interesting.

291
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,660
You're very interesting.

292
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,880
If I had known this,

293
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:54,750
I should have gone with you.

294
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:58,040
If you went,
there would just be one more bandage.

295
00:21:58,180 --> 00:21:59,710
I was a detective.

296
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:01,680
Prof.

297
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,240
I have reason to believe

298
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:04,700
that Qi Yan's twin brother

299
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,180
lived until 5 years ago

300
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,920
and didn't die young.

301
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:10,590
It's just that we didn't ask further

302
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,920
regarding the twins.

303
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,860
There probably won't be more breakthroughs

304
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,320
through Qi Zhen anymore.

305
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,750
These are the people
I'm afraid of encountering—

306
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:23,740
they would rather commit suicide

307
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:25,450
than say another word.

308
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:27,830
But Qi Yan is no longer

309
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:29,160
a blurry figure.

310
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,310
He has a brother who died because of him,

311
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:34,170
a mother who fears him extremely,

312
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:36,520
and a father his mother sees as an animal.

313
00:22:37,830 --> 00:22:40,160
This information is very important to us.

314
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,760
Knowing what happened to him

315
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:44,530
will make it easier to find his weakness.

316
00:22:46,030 --> 00:22:47,200
Anyway,

317
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,380
this trip to Huaiguang

318
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,980
still yielded a major breakthrough.

319
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:55,520
But I really didn't imagine

320
00:22:55,620 --> 00:22:57,680
Qi Zhen could live such a normal life.

321
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,210
With Qi Yan's abilities,

322
00:22:59,210 --> 00:23:01,310
it would be very easy
for him to find Qi Zhen.

323
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,770
But he neither hurt Qi Zhen

324
00:23:03,070 --> 00:23:04,390
nor Chief Jian.

325
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:05,880
Instead, he hurt

326
00:23:06,030 --> 00:23:07,160
unrelated people.

327
00:23:07,750 --> 00:23:09,070
Maybe it's because

328
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:13,520
he couldn't bring himself
to hurt his own mother,

329
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:16,880
so he needed to find

330
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:17,790
substitutes.

331
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:19,680
The women he killed

332
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,180
were the substitutes.

333
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:24,640
Yao Weihai,

334
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:26,200
Cangfeng,

335
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,780
and your brother—

336
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,930
they were all substitutes.

337
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:39,710
And I don't think
Qi Zhen lived a peaceful life.

338
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:41,070
Irritability

339
00:23:41,260 --> 00:23:43,390
is a typical symptom of neurasthenia.

340
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,270
She must have been in a state of tension

341
00:23:45,270 --> 00:23:46,750
and high pressure for a long time.

342
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:47,640
Even living

343
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,170
with a police station chief

344
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:51,880
can't completely eliminate her fear.

345
00:23:51,940 --> 00:23:54,140
It shows how much pressure she is under.

346
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:56,120
And those killed by Qi Yan

347
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,510
were both targets

348
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,510
and tools.

349
00:24:00,580 --> 00:24:01,260
So

350
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:05,300
he is using his evil deeds
to torture his mother.

351
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,400
No wonder Qi Zhen

352
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,200
refused to admit she was Qi Zhen.

353
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:12,750
She didn't want to hear or say anything

354
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,480
because she completely denies

355
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,550
having this son

356
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:16,550
and also the existence

357
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:17,920
of this whole thing.

358
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,630
I strangled his son to death.

359
00:24:21,550 --> 00:24:23,030
His son died long ago.

360
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,750
She might have really tried

361
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:26,830
to strangle Qi Yan.

362
00:24:27,490 --> 00:24:29,010
We analyzed early on

363
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:31,550
that Qi Yan was abandoned by his mother.

364
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:32,950
What kind of abandonment

365
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:35,590
could be more thorough and evil
than killing your own child

366
00:24:35,590 --> 00:24:36,310
with your

367
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:37,440
own hands?

368
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,220
Mentor sent a message.

369
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:49,170
What did he say?

370
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:50,450
He said,

371
00:24:50,810 --> 00:24:52,440
"Don't alert Jian Liang anymore.

372
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,300
I'll follow up.

373
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:55,400
You two come back when you're done.

374
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:56,350
Stay safe."

375
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:01,180
The enemy is in the dark
and we are in the open.

376
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,640
You must be careful.

377
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:13,310
Put the chair here.

378
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:17,290
Put the TV here. Come on.

379
00:25:17,310 --> 00:25:18,270
Put it here.

380
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:20,720
Put the TV here.

381
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:21,590
Right.

382
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,310
Okay, put the stereo here.

383
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:25,770
Right, put all the vegetables
in the fridge.

384
00:25:29,510 --> 00:25:31,160
Okay, put the beer here.

385
00:25:31,350 --> 00:25:32,310
Right.

386
00:25:33,810 --> 00:25:35,610
Put the microwave on that table.

387
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,930
It looks a bit more like a home
with this arrangement.

388
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,440
This guy is something.

389
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,290
He just got paid and

390
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:03,530
he already spent it all.

391
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,350
What did he buy?

392
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,620
A sports betting website?

393
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:10,890
He bet on a game.

394
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,160
Investigate this website.

395
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,420
Keep a close eye on him.

396
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,400
Okay.

397
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,030
Team Blues

398
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:37,740
versus Team Damien.

399
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:40,880
[Team Blues] [Team Damien]

400
00:27:43,570 --> 00:27:44,330
Zhou Jin.

401
00:27:44,350 --> 00:27:45,080
You're back.

402
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,040
Zhou Jin!

403
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:48,270
We need one more person
for the martial arts friendlies.

404
00:27:48,270 --> 00:27:49,030
Sign up.

405
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:50,240
Have you forgotten?

406
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:52,000
I performed too well last year.

407
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,860
They unilaterally banned me.

408
00:27:54,830 --> 00:27:55,830
Have Zhao Ping go.

409
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,610
Are you going to look for Chief Tan?

410
00:27:59,270 --> 00:28:00,580
He has a cold,
so I made him some medicine.

411
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:01,380
Take it to him.

412
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:03,750
He has a cold?

413
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:04,790
Zhou Jin.

414
00:28:05,190 --> 00:28:07,110
You went on a business trip
and had a honeymoon along the way—

415
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:08,200
how was it?

416
00:28:08,950 --> 00:28:10,440
Watch your mouth.

417
00:28:10,470 --> 00:28:12,200
What do they have to do with you?

418
00:28:12,270 --> 00:28:13,270
Just do your job.

419
00:28:13,770 --> 00:28:15,330
I'm just curious.

420
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:16,680
You are so gossipy.

421
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:18,650
Oh, right.

422
00:28:18,650 --> 00:28:20,220
How's the investigation going?

423
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:21,200
There's no progress.

424
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,350
We're discussing a new approach.

425
00:28:22,350 --> 00:28:23,610
Did you find anything?

426
00:28:25,790 --> 00:28:27,240
Not really.

427
00:28:29,430 --> 00:28:30,640
Make sure he drinks it.

428
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,440
I'm off, then.

429
00:28:34,110 --> 00:28:34,880
Sign up.

430
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:36,830
Sign up, everyone.

431
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:39,720
Dan.

432
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,790
Count... me out.

433
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:45,300
You were in the SWAT team;
what are you afraid of?

434
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:46,710
That's in the past.

435
00:28:46,730 --> 00:28:48,350
I'm afraid I'll disgrace our team.

436
00:28:48,350 --> 00:28:49,270
So you mean,

437
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:50,720
I should go for you? How's that?

438
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:52,110
You're guilt-tripping me. Guilt-tripping!

439
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:52,920
I-I'll go.

440
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:54,480
I didn't touch her. I-I didn't.

441
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:55,740
I wrote your name down.

442
00:28:56,510 --> 00:28:57,100
Sir.

443
00:28:58,030 --> 00:28:59,670
Dan made this medicine for you.

444
00:28:59,670 --> 00:29:02,200
She told me
I have to make sure you drink it all.

445
00:29:03,210 --> 00:29:03,810
By the way,

446
00:29:04,350 --> 00:29:05,680
what's the latest clue?

447
00:29:05,790 --> 00:29:07,640
It seems no one outside knows.

448
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:09,120
It's a secret for now.

449
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:25,290
Did you find out Qi Zhen's real identity?

450
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,680
So far,

451
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,720
there's no record of Qi Zhen.

452
00:29:29,190 --> 00:29:30,390
How is that possible?

453
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:33,370
Chief Jian's wife is clearly Qi Zhen.

454
00:29:33,370 --> 00:29:35,440
After the Women's Federation saved her,

455
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,160
she claimed she had amnesia

456
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:38,590
and couldn't remember anything.

457
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:40,250
Even her name was given later.

458
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:44,000
We basically don't know anything
about her past,

459
00:29:44,030 --> 00:29:46,630
and there is no way
to track down her relatives.

460
00:29:50,310 --> 00:29:51,550
Then what's the clue?

461
00:29:58,270 --> 00:29:59,470
Look at this message.

462
00:29:59,750 --> 00:30:01,010
Does it mean anything?

463
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:07,670
Illegal sports betting?

464
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:10,760
It's a cipher for the goods trading
time and place.

465
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:17,080
The afternoon of October 11th.

466
00:30:17,990 --> 00:30:19,270
3:4...

467
00:30:20,470 --> 00:30:21,620
3:40 PM.

468
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:23,790
Or it could be 3:04 PM too.

469
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:26,210
A place starting with "B."

470
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:27,590
95...

471
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:28,880
No. 95?

472
00:30:29,030 --> 00:30:30,000
Bus 95?

473
00:30:33,350 --> 00:30:34,750
Where did this come from?

474
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,480
It's from Cangfeng.

475
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:37,310
Cangfeng?

476
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:39,930
Isn't Cangfeng Meng Junfeng?

477
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,560
But Meng Junfeng already...

478
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,310
Could you tell me

479
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:46,590
who this Cangfeng is?

480
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:50,720
I can only reveal

481
00:30:50,770 --> 00:30:52,120
a Cangfeng's identity

482
00:30:52,890 --> 00:30:54,470
when they are completely exposed,

483
00:30:54,470 --> 00:30:55,580
confirmed dead,

484
00:30:56,830 --> 00:30:58,090
or return victorious.

485
00:30:58,590 --> 00:30:59,870
After the operation begins,

486
00:30:59,870 --> 00:31:01,510
I will leave the phone with you.

487
00:31:01,510 --> 00:31:03,110
As long as Cangfeng is alive,

488
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:05,070
he will definitely contact me.

489
00:31:05,070 --> 00:31:06,400
If the operation doesn't go well,

490
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,200
you take over.

491
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:10,010
The contact method
is in the safe in my office.

492
00:31:10,070 --> 00:31:10,920
The password is

493
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,830
951018.

494
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,080
If something happens to Cangfeng,

495
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:16,750
the confidential file
will be decrypted for you,

496
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:18,810
and you will naturally know who he is.

497
00:31:19,030 --> 00:31:20,090
This is top secret.

498
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:23,200
Meng Junfeng is definitely one.

499
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:24,640
But,

500
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,420
from beginning to end,

501
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,720
I've never asked Mr. Yao

502
00:31:29,350 --> 00:31:31,110
how many Cangfengs there are,

503
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:33,750
and if there could be
more than one of them?

504
00:31:34,310 --> 00:31:35,270
Is it possible

505
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:36,610
that it's Jiang Cheng?

506
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,680
That's why I called you over.

507
00:31:42,180 --> 00:31:42,990
Look at this.

508
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,810
This is a virtual overseas website

509
00:31:46,950 --> 00:31:48,420
set up by Mr. Yao.

510
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,860
Cangfeng contacts him by placing bets

511
00:31:52,070 --> 00:31:53,270
on football matches.

512
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:01,710
Map.

513
00:32:02,370 --> 00:32:03,170
Map?

514
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:18,680
When Jiang Cheng and I were kids,

515
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:20,640
we used this method to play hide-and-seek.

516
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:21,680
95 bets.

517
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:22,960
95.

518
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:24,400
Xiali Reservoir.

519
00:32:38,870 --> 00:32:40,720
Mentor, what are you thinking?

520
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,440
Tell me your thoughts.

521
00:32:46,010 --> 00:32:47,200
This is the only

522
00:32:47,220 --> 00:32:48,480
direct clue we can get.

523
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:50,140
If we don't go and see,

524
00:32:50,650 --> 00:32:51,710
we can never be sure

525
00:32:51,730 --> 00:32:53,360
if our speculation is right.

526
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:56,640
What is Professor Jiang

527
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:57,480
busy with?

528
00:32:59,030 --> 00:33:00,430
He's teaching at school.

529
00:33:00,910 --> 00:33:02,910
Making up for the classes he missed.

530
00:33:03,380 --> 00:33:04,760
I would like him
to come and give some advice.

531
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:05,760
What do you think?

532
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:07,480
Sure.

533
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,440
He is trustworthy.

534
00:33:10,150 --> 00:33:11,550
I know he is trustworthy.

535
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,070
What I mean is—

536
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,720
is it appropriate for him

537
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:17,860
to be involved in this?

538
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:21,640
Is there anything inappropriate about it?

539
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:24,090
Since you,
the person involved, don't mind,

540
00:33:24,090 --> 00:33:25,690
I don't need to worry either.

541
00:33:25,750 --> 00:33:27,480
Come on, give him a call.

542
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,400
Those who preside over a provincial-level
or higher research project

543
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,560
and achieve great research results

544
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,960
during the tenure
of an associate professor

545
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,960
can become a full professor

546
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,560
without waiting for 5 years.

547
00:33:44,990 --> 00:33:46,450
You should consider this.

548
00:33:46,770 --> 00:33:47,320
Also

549
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:49,280
pay attention to your attendance.

550
00:33:52,350 --> 00:33:52,750
Jiang,

551
00:33:53,590 --> 00:33:54,750
you don't look well.

552
00:33:56,530 --> 00:33:57,870
I have a throbbing nerve pain.

553
00:33:57,870 --> 00:33:59,880
I've been sleeping too little lately.

554
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:02,140
It's indeed too tiring for you
to be working for both sides.

555
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:03,850
[Wife]

556
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:06,880
Please excuse me.

557
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:08,400
I'll head off first.

558
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:08,960
Okay.

559
00:34:26,670 --> 00:34:27,320
Honey.

560
00:34:27,590 --> 00:34:29,320
It's not your wife. It's Tan.

561
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,199
Professor Jiang.

562
00:34:34,590 --> 00:34:36,590
I need to bother you with something.

563
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:39,030
Is something wrong with the team?

564
00:34:39,030 --> 00:34:41,230
See if you can take a leave and come over.

565
00:34:43,190 --> 00:34:44,719
I'll try to get there as soon as possible.

566
00:34:44,719 --> 00:34:45,080
Okay.

567
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:46,520
Oh, right.

568
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,110
I'll give you

569
00:34:48,230 --> 00:34:49,489
a heads-up in advance.

570
00:34:49,550 --> 00:34:50,400
It's about

571
00:34:50,670 --> 00:34:51,880
Jiang Cheng.

572
00:34:55,230 --> 00:34:55,630
Okay.

573
00:34:58,280 --> 00:34:58,880
Chief Tan.

574
00:34:59,260 --> 00:35:00,520
Is Zhou Jin next to you?

575
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,550
Yes, yes.

576
00:35:02,030 --> 00:35:02,880
Hold on.

577
00:35:07,110 --> 00:35:07,920
Hansheng.

578
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:18,150
Maybe he's rushing over.

579
00:35:50,610 --> 00:35:53,360
[Yatou Pharmaceutical Factory]

580
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:03,380
Are we sure
we're only giving this tomorrow?

581
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,990
I've already settled it with them.

582
00:36:06,990 --> 00:36:10,190
We'll give them a little first
for them to check the goods.

583
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,480
Where did you agree to meet?

584
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:14,010
3:30 PM at Xiali Reservoir.

585
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:17,320
Remember

586
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,060
to wear a mask and a hat.

587
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:20,930
I know. And sunglasses too.

588
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:22,260
It's sunny over there.

589
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:24,280
I'll pick a few people to go with you.

590
00:36:24,780 --> 00:36:26,410
That way, if anything happens,

591
00:36:26,410 --> 00:36:27,610
they can help you out.

592
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,230
There's no need.

593
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:31,170
The fewer people, the simpler.

594
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:32,550
Just listen to me.

595
00:36:33,470 --> 00:36:35,200
If you get caught by the police,

596
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,510
we're all doomed.

597
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:39,830
How are they going to help me?

598
00:36:39,860 --> 00:36:41,130
By shooting me dead

599
00:36:41,150 --> 00:36:42,680
before the police catch me?

600
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,800
Just listen to Boss He.

601
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,100
It's Old Scorpion's request.

602
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:53,110
All right.

603
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:54,450
All right.

604
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,050
I'm not sure.

605
00:37:19,530 --> 00:37:20,660
Not sure about what?

606
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:26,040
Let's assume he means

607
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:28,060
to meet at Xiali Reservoir

608
00:37:28,170 --> 00:37:29,300
at 3:40 PM tomorrow.

609
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:32,160
But the previous Jingang operation

610
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:33,290
is a lesson learned.

611
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:35,440
They first used Cangfeng

612
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,170
to pass fake news to the police,

613
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:39,130
and then lured us into a trap.

614
00:37:40,090 --> 00:37:42,150
I don't dare to make a hasty judgment.

615
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:46,640
That's exactly what I'm worried about too.

616
00:37:47,090 --> 00:37:49,150
The tragedy of the Jingang operation

617
00:37:49,150 --> 00:37:50,550
must never happen again.

618
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:52,900
Is Jiang Cheng

619
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:56,550
another Cangfeng?

620
00:37:57,610 --> 00:37:58,490
If he is,

621
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:02,490
how do we explain
the fingerprints on the gun?

622
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:03,090
Also,

623
00:38:04,410 --> 00:38:05,850
we have no idea

624
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,570
whether he actually established contact

625
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:09,720
with Leader Yao.

626
00:38:10,790 --> 00:38:11,850
Taking a step back,

627
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:14,460
even if he is another Cangfeng,

628
00:38:15,310 --> 00:38:16,570
after all these years,

629
00:38:18,750 --> 00:38:20,210
could there be no changes?

630
00:38:23,050 --> 00:38:23,840
Let me go.

631
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,770
This is indeed Jiang Cheng's way

632
00:38:26,910 --> 00:38:28,710
of marking a map's coordinates.

633
00:38:29,360 --> 00:38:31,160
Whether he works for Leader Yao or not,

634
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:32,310
there are only two possibilities.

635
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:32,950
First,

636
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:34,260
it's another trap.

637
00:38:34,390 --> 00:38:34,960
Second,

638
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,120
he has something

639
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:37,620
to tell the police.

640
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,790
Whichever it is,

641
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:41,870
if I go,

642
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,310
at least Jiang Cheng won't kill me.

643
00:38:44,310 --> 00:38:45,570
Don't be so confident.

644
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:50,800
Right, right.

645
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,160
Don't be so rash.

646
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:54,200
Where does your confidence come from?

647
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:54,750
Anyway,

648
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,420
we need

649
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:57,910
to be careful.

650
00:38:59,750 --> 00:39:01,120
We can't act rashly.

651
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:03,080
Right?

652
00:39:20,590 --> 00:39:21,260
Cheng,

653
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,560
that guy in white
over there looks like it.

654
00:39:24,940 --> 00:39:26,480
Why are you staring at other people?

655
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:27,830
Watch your fishing rod.

656
00:39:41,700 --> 00:39:42,550
Do you see him?

657
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:44,050
I'm not sure yet.

658
00:39:58,770 --> 00:40:00,290
Well, do you recognize me?

659
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,850
Are you trying to be a thief?

660
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,200
I'm stalking a thief.

661
00:40:04,390 --> 00:40:05,600
No one can tell, right?

662
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:06,390
It's perfect.

663
00:40:06,390 --> 00:40:07,520
Even a ghost couldn't recognize you.

664
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,750
Then I won't call you Jin anymore.

665
00:40:08,750 --> 00:40:10,010
I'll call you ghostie.

666
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:18,150
I can confirm

667
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:19,680
this guy is Jiang Cheng.

668
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:21,050
Yes, I see him.

669
00:40:25,610 --> 00:40:26,610
Should we go over?

670
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:29,000
There are too many people.

671
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,070
Let's wait.

672
00:40:39,490 --> 00:40:40,520
Did you catch all these?

673
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:41,040
Yes.

674
00:40:47,630 --> 00:40:49,030
Are they making the deal?

675
00:40:49,140 --> 00:40:49,700
Yes.

676
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:53,430
It's time.

677
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:57,980
You're quite good.

678
00:40:58,390 --> 00:40:59,320
Not bad, I guess.

679
00:41:24,620 --> 00:41:25,620
Should we go over?

680
00:41:26,230 --> 00:41:26,840
Let's go.

681
00:41:28,020 --> 00:41:29,350
Let's go down together.

682
00:41:29,450 --> 00:41:31,100
You get as close to him as possible.

683
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:32,770
Show up in his line of sight,

684
00:41:33,060 --> 00:41:34,390
but don't make contact.

685
00:41:37,350 --> 00:41:38,220
Wait, wait.

686
00:41:42,270 --> 00:41:44,470
The guy who just made the deal is coming.

687
00:41:47,350 --> 00:41:48,410
Should we take him?

688
00:41:48,740 --> 00:41:50,270
Let's not alert him for now.

689
00:41:53,170 --> 00:41:53,700
Let's go.

690
00:41:57,600 --> 00:41:58,930
Should we go?

691
00:42:00,490 --> 00:42:01,450
What's the rush?

692
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:03,840
It's too obvious if we follow too closely.

693
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:04,320
Right.

694
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:15,210
Send the license plate
and car model to Bai Yang.

695
00:42:15,210 --> 00:42:16,410
Have him check it.

696
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:17,580
Yes.
